28/01/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski, accompanied by Justice Minister Meri Mladenovska Georgievska, met on Thursday (27 January) with the President of the Supreme Court Dane Iliev, President of the Macedonian Judges Association Agim Miftari and other senior representatives of judiciary sector.
They discussed reforms needed in the sector and the need to renovate court and prosecution buildings.
Buckovski accepted their request to hire 140 new judges in 2005.
(MIA, Makfax - 27/01/05)
